is M D  from Harvard Medical School and his Ph D  in political philosophy from Harvard University  He has published more than     articles on health care reform  research ethics and end of life care  and is the most widely cited bioethicist  His most recent book quality  more patient focused  and lower cost care  and from their examples distills    transformational practices that could transform the entire healthcare sector He was elected to the National Academy of Medicine and the American Academy of Arts and Sciences  He is a      recipient of the Dan David Prize in the category of bioethics  an honor recognizing innovative and interdisciplinary research that cuts across traditional boundaries and paradigms Eric Smith Eric Smith is regional president of Fifth Third Bank  Chicago  which includes more than      billion in assets  In this role  he is responsible for the growth and strategic alignment of commercial  wealth and asset management and consumer businesses to deliver distinctive value to customers and community impact in the region Smith joined Fifth Third in October      from JPMorgan Chase  where he most recently served as chief financial officer of middle market banking  Prior to assuming that role in       he was a managing director in the investment bank  where he served as the head of the North American Food and Beverage Group  He also was responsible for advising Fortune     consumer product companies on merger and acquisition transactions as well as debt and equity underwritings Smith has more than    years of banking experience and began his career with Merrill Lynch as a financial analyst in public finance Smith currently serves as the chairman of the board for the Chicago Urban League  Robert H  Likewise To accommodate guests who cannot attend  UIC will stream both commencements stream Click here for complete details about fall commencement at UIC details          njboynes uic edu n n n nCategories n nAlumni  Campus  n Contact          njboynes u